If this design looks familiar it’s because I used it as my logo for years too. ⁣

#debbiebean #stainedglass #stainedglassart #stainedglassartist #leadedglass

47 🎉⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I woke up this morning and when I looked in the mirror I thought to myself, take a picture to remember what 47 feels like. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
46 was rough. The first year without my Dad. I said goodbye to my cat Bella only a few months after he died and all while running this small business that I started 9 years ago. There were some definite high points this past year too! Grief is a wild ride and there’s plenty of highs to counter the lows, but I’m looking forward to a quiet end of the year, so I can take some down time and rest. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Thank you to everyone who has continued to support the work I do and my friends who carry me through everything. I don’t do this shit alone and I’m grateful that I have cheerleaders in my corner every day like my hubs who is smartly not on here and all of you that are. ♐️🏹🔥♐️🏹🔥
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#happybirthdaytome #debbiebean #sagittarius

Opened my kiln this am and found a mess. Lost all the work I made and spent half the day getting glass out of my kiln floor and figuring out what happened.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
On the flip side…I really love what my kiln shelf looks like now and want to make some more work like this intentionally once my kiln is back up and running. ⁣
⁣
Also, it reminds me of a goth version of the album artwork for @catpowerofficial The Covers Record. ⁣🎶

This has been an unusual year for me. I lost my father a day before my birthday in December of 2021 and then said goodbye to our cat Bella in March of this year. While we continued to be busy in the studio, as anyone that has gone through the first year of grieving can attest to, it has been at times a challenging period of firsts for me.⁣
⁣
I didn’t post a lot this year because that was just one of the things that felt overwhelming to me, but while reflecting on this past year I realized there was a lot of joy and thought why not share that with all of you!⁣
⁣
I spent a very fun evening with @denvirenterprises and @radfurniture in October to learn more about their process and try my hand at some welding. Spoiler alert! I wasn’t very good at it right away. I think it’s important to remember that it’s ok to suck at something in the beginning because that’s how we learn. I was just stoked to spend time with our friends and see their workshop that we created our coffee table with!!
⁣
⁣
#debbiebean #stainedglass #radfurniture #denvirenterprises #frogtown

Finally got my kiln back up and running and I’ve been thinking about what I want to focus on this year when this photo popped up.  This was a custom piece I created years ago and I remember at the time thinking that I really wanted to explore more of this type of work and then got caught up doing all the other things. ⁣
⁣
So perhaps now is a good time to re-examine what new worlds I can conjure up in my studio. ⁣what do you think?
⁣
⁣

Working on a couple of projects and going over reference photos of previous jobs when I  came across this photo. I love that you can see some of the rainbows in the iridescent glass. ⁣
⁣
I designed this piece to compliment the home while being renovated to work with the lines in the new door and exterior. It was important that the stained glass captured the client’s joyful and expressive personality while not feeling busy and competing with the overall redesign of the home.⁣
⁣
I always love working with color, but this is a good example of how lead lines and textured glass can be just as visually inspired as colored stained glass.⁣
⁣
⁣

I found my very first stained glass piece I made 30 years ago while we were cleaning this weekend. 🤯⁣
⁣
True story. I ditched school so much that I didn’t have enough credits to graduate and ended up taking a stained glass class in night school. It’s clearly poorly made, but this first attempt is what laid the foundation for my career years later. ⁣
⁣
I was 100% inspired by @neilhimself ‘s character Death from @thesandmanofficial for this design 🖤🖤🖤⁣

📣BIG ANNOUNCEMENT📣⁣
⁣
I am pausing the production of my open edition pieces. Over the past 9 years, I've diligently cultivated a substantial online presence and wide-reaching global network of over 200 stockists. The progress I've achieved has far surpassed my initial aspirations. Though this shift may appear sudden, I am thrilled to redirect my studio's focus towards crafting more bespoke, one-of-a-kind creations. So, for now, I am stepping back from managing my wholesale and online store operations to channel my energy into my current projects and exciting new artistic pursuits.⁣
⁣
🛍️ All remaining inventory is now available in my online shop with only a few items left as my email subscribers were the first to know of this big change.⁣ UPDATE - SOLD OUT.
⁣
SO WHAT NOW?⁣
⁣
📚 Despite the studio's quiet exterior, I've been immersing myself in diverse courses to elevate my stained glass craftsmanship and delve into innovative experimental pieces.⁣
⁣
🔴I've also taken on more commercial and residential projects and have a full studio calendar for the months ahead.⁣
⁣
📧GET IN TOUCH📧⁣
If you are interested in custom work, reach out on my website. Link in profile.
⁣
🙏🏻A deep bow of gratitude to @emmy_lou_hue . I couldn’t imagine my studio without her these past years. I am so excited for her new journey.
⁣
❤️As always, I am deeply grateful for the ongoing support and I am excited to continue sharing my journey with all of you—stay tuned for more artistic explorations! ❤️

This panel is from of a custom residential project I completed for a dream client. They were updating the sidelights on their home and trusted me to come up with a design to transform their entryway.⁣
⁣
I created a pair of stained glass panels that when illuminated create kaleidoscopic shadows while still maintaining their privacy by using a combination of glass opacities and textures.⁣
⁣
⁣
I will have more photos once the space is completed but wanted to share a little teaser of what I created. And yes, it’s taller than me 😂⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#debbiebean #stainedglass #stainedglasswindow #madeinla

Beautiful Mess 🌈⁣
⁣
Came across this photo I took while making this panel. I love working with lead and all the ways you have to plan out your fabrication process and watching your design unfold in front of you. ⁣
⁣
This was a real fun one to work on because it had so many interesting curves that I designed. I wanted the lead lines to play an important role in the finished piece. My first thought when I completed this panel was, “ When can I create another piece in this style?!”⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#debbiebean #stainedglass #madeinla #stainedglassartist

From the archives 🌈⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I can’t believe I never posted this photo of a magical client’s bedroom door that I did. They wanted to keep the original door but turn it into a rainbow portal to the outside. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I started with iridescent glass at the top for whimsy and used progressively darker glass towards the bottom for drama. You get visibility at eye level and some privacy at the bottom. It’s all about balance and creating colorful shadows when the sun hits ☀️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Who wouldn’t want to wake up here?!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#rainbowconnection #debbiebean #stainedglass #madeinla #stainedglassartist
